<Layout title="Frank Li | Home">
  <div class="flex flex-col gap-12">
    <div class="text-justify">
      <Heading>ABOUT</Heading>
      <p>
        I am a senior undergraduate student pursuing a degree in Computer
        Science at the
        <TextLink href="https://cs.uw.edu/">University of Washington</TextLink>,
        with an anticipated graduation date of spring 2026. As of June 2023, I
        have been working as a Jr. SDE III at
        <TextLink href="https://www.amazon.com">Amazon</TextLink>, having
        progressed from levels I and II. I work full-time during the holidays,
        and part-time during the school year. This upcoming summer, I will be
        interning as a Software Engineer at
        <TextLink href="https://www.twosigma.com">Two Sigma</TextLink> in New York
        City, followed by an internship as a System Software Engineer at
        <TextLink href="https://nvidia.com">NVIDIA</TextLink> in Santa Clara during
        the fall.
      </p>
      <br />
      <p>
        My primary career aspiration is in software engineering, but I have also
        engaged in computer science research projects. Notably, I contributed to
        medical image segmentation research at the
        <TextLink href="https://www.kurtlab.com/">Kurt Lab</TextLink>, utilizing
        U-Net and vision transformers, and collaborated with
        <TextLink href="https://faculty.washington.edu/dzhao/"
          >Dr. Dongfang Zhao</TextLink
        >
        in the <TextLink href="https://hpdic.github.io/">HPDIC Lab</TextLink> on
        efficient multi-vector query of vector databases.
      </p>
      <br />
      <p>
        Currently working on some stuff using the <TextLink
          href="https://modelcontextprotocol.io"
          >model context protocol</TextLink
        >.
      </p>
